{
  "texts": [
    "This step is akin to the reverse stress testing on financial portfolios.",
    "Step 3 backpropagates these loss predictions through the entire layered network.",
    "This step is the important extension that allows for previous reverse stress testing methodologies to be applied to supply chains.",
    "Step 4 repeats Step 2, but produces other less likely, but still probable, loss scenarios for each layer in the network.",
    "While the most likely scenarios produced by the first run of Steps 2 and 3 are important, this methodology is intended to account for other scenarios that may be possible."
  ]
}